<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-17T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-17T11:00:00-05:00" n="249" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1910</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-17T17:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 17, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 17, 4.18
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1950. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName> tells me
                                today, in reply to an inquiry I made of him as to the British
                                Government’s answer to the Austrian peace proposal, that your answer
                                published in today’s evening papers so completely meets with his
                                views that he will probably not follow with idea he had tentatively
                                formed of concerting with our co-belligerents in forming a joint
                                answer. This came out quite informally as conversation and I
                                transmit it at once for your information. If anything further
                                develops I shall inform you.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>